    <div>

        <p><b>16. <i>CERTIFICATION REGARDINGPOLITICALCONTRIBUTIONS, FEES, AND COMMISSIONS (<a href='http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?c=ecfr&SID=9f40509b0e3da13737d77a645b79f912&rgn=div5&view=text&node=22:1.0.1.13.67&idno=22'> ITAR PART 130</a>)</i></b></p>

        <p>Please note 22 CFR 130.12(b) requires Supplier to respond to this section <b>within 20 days</b>, unless Supplier provides the information directly to the U.S. State Department in accordance with 22 CFR 130.12(c). U.S. law requires Honeywell to inform the Department of State if we have not received a response within 25 days of this request. Additionally, 22 CFR 130.14 requires Supplier to maintain the records upon which the information below is based for a minimum of five (5) years from the date of the report. </p>

        <p>A. <i>SUPPLIER</i> certifies it <b>SELLS</b> defense articles, technical data, and/or defense services to Honeywell that are:  (1) controlled for export under U.S. International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR) (22 CFR Parts 120-130); (2) valued in an amount of $500,000 or greater; and (3) for delivery (or incorporation into another product for delivery) to, or for the use of, the armed forces of an international organization or a country other than the United States. </p>
        
        <p style ="margin-left:20px">
            <b style ="margin-left:40px"><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox56/> YES </b>
            <b style ="margin-left:20px"><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox57/> NO </b>
        </p>

        <p> B. <i>SUPPLIER</i> certifies it has paid, offered to pay, or agreed to pay any "fees", "commisions", or "political contributions" as defined in 22 CFR § 130.5 and 22 CFR § 130.6 in connection with the sale of defense articles, technical data, and/or defense services to Honeywell. </p>
        
        <p style ="margin-left:20px">
